ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How many days in the past 30 days did you have a panic attack?
Notes: Number of days in a month

ElementDescription: When do your panic attacks usually occur?
Notes: 1= All of your attacks occur ''out of the blue''; 2= Some of your attacks occur ''out of the blue'' and others in situations where you have a strong fear or are in real danger; 3= All of your attacks occur in situations where you have a strong fear or are in real danger

ElementDescription: How many ''out of the blue'' panic attacks did you have in the past 30 days?
Notes: Number of panic attacks in a month

Which of the following reactions did you usually have during attacks? Chills or heat sensations
Which of the following reactions did you usually have during attacks? Numbness or tingling
Which of the following reactions did you usually have during attacks? Fear of losing control or going crazy
Which of the following reactions did you usually have during attacks? Fear of dying

Which of the following reactions did you usually have during attacks? Feeling like things around you were unreal, like a dream, or like you were not really there, like you were watching a movie of yourself

After having an ''out of the blue'' panic attack, did you ever have a time lasting 1 month or longer when you often worried that you might have another attack or that something terrible might happen because of the attacks like an accident, heart attack, or that you might lose control?

After having a panic attack, did you ever have a time lasting 1 month or longer when you often worried that you might have another attack or that something terrible might happen because of the attacks like an accident, heart attack, or that you might lose control?
How old were you the very first time you had an ''out of the blue'' panic attack?
About how many different years in your life did you have at least one of these ''out of the blue'' attacks?
Notes: Total number of years in your lifetime

ElementDescription: How many months in the past 12 did you have ''out of the blue'' panic attacks?
Notes: Total number of months in the past year
